{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01Ct52mCbEkRsgY8EkpEJJzU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RWdsJHEZNV1tdsBYj5RkGU","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"git -C /tmp/fdb-pack6G-G3_5-20260504T144523Z commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\ndiag(G3_5): per-reader-worker DBSTATUS_CACHE_* telemetry helper\n\nPack 6.G G.3.5 — debug-only `ReaderRequest::CacheStatus` broadcast +\n`Engine::cache_status_per_worker_for_test`. Mirrors G.1's\n`LookasideStatus` shape: each reader worker reads its own\nSQLITE_DBSTATUS_CACHE_HIT / _MISS / _USED via raw FFI and replies on a\noneshot channel. Reset flag = 0 (counters monotonic; callers compute\npre/post deltas).\n\nAdds an `#[ignore]`-gated diagnostic test\n`g3_5_cache_pressure_telemetry` that warms the AC-020 fixture, snapshots\neach worker, runs one concurrent body, snapshots again, and writes a\nsidecar JSON to G3_5_OUTPUT_PATH so the orchestrator can build the\nphase JSON without re-running. Test is `#[cfg(debug_assertions)]`-gated\nto keep release builds buildable (the helper accessor is itself\ndebug-only per the F.0 / G.1 convention).\n\nNo production code path changes, no PRAGMA changes, no public surface\nexpansion outside `#[cfg(debug_assertions)] #[doc(hidden)]`. AC-017 +\nAC-018 stay green.\nEOF\n)\"","description":"commit"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":361,"cache_read_input_tokens":92966,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":361},"output_tokens":72,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"485c34a8-dceb-42a9-9d76-fb4335ae2dfc","uuid":"9dab7579-0391-47bc-b400-0a6817a2e43d"}
